Key Match Events: Rassie van der Dussen scored 133 runs
Marco Jansen took 3 wickets for 31 runs
Keshav Maharaj took 4 wickets for 46 runs
Post-Match Reflections: Temba Bavuma: 'Clinical display I would say'
Rassie van der Dussen: 'We were speaking about 300-320 at one stage in the middle but we've seen so often in the last 12-18 months what the guys coming in can do'
Miscellaneous Highlights: South Africa beat New Zealand by 190 runs
South Africa leapfrogged India to the top of the standings
New Zealand are still in the hunt for a place in the semi-finals in fourth
Others: The match took place at the MCA Stadium in Pune
Tim Southee returned to competitive action after right thumb surgery in September
Matt Henry was unavailable due to a right hamstring problem
Jimmy Neesham was struck on the hand while stopping a ball off his own bowling
